Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with
@salt{0.25%tsp} for the pasta.

Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips
then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm pieces.

Pop both onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Toss to coat, spread out and roast on the top shelf until soft,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Add the @linguine{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook until tender,
~{12%minutes} then drain in a #colander{}. Pop back in the pan, drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you
have one). Finely chop the @chives{1} (or use #scissors{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. When hot, add
the garlic and cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato puree{30%g}, followed by the
@finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1%can}, @vegetable stock powder{1},
@sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and @water{500%ml}.

Add a pinch of @sugar{pinch} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thick and tomatoey,
~{4-5%minutes}.

When they are ready, combine the roasted veggies, cooked pasta and sauce in
whichever pan is the largest.

Stir in half the chives and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.
> TIP: Add a splash more water if it seems a bit dry! Season to taste with salt
> and pepper if needed.

Serve in #bowls{}. Finish with the @walnuts{20}(chopped) and a sprinkling of
the remaining chives and cheese. Enjoy!